Hey it would be great to modify it as a NSF-&gt;SPC converter so you could litsen it as simple .spc<br />Also I now understand why it did work with so few of my works : The SNES CPU runs the code "as-it" without any emulation, and the host programm overwrites some zeropage locations. It would have been better (but much slower) to write a true emulator here.<br /><br />In the end the sound would be much better if a lower sample was used for square so it doesn't sound so muffled, and if a sample would be used for noise instead of noise.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sun Nov 01, 2009 10:09 am</p><hr />
