<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5688&amp;p=51868#p51868"><![CDATA[
$4015 can be used to re-trigger DPCM (not to pause though).  But yeah it's like Bregalad said, a lot of stuff takes effect when those upper registers for each channel are changed.<br /><br />If it's any help for reference I could re-upload the source my NES sound emulator for SNES.  The length counters and everything clocked at 60hz is on the 65c816, but the sweeps, linear counter, etc. are in SPC asm and rely on the SPC timers.  Not that it's perfect emulation, but it's very close (only 1 or 2 NSFs play wrong, but most of them don't use the hardware effects and stuff anyways).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Thu Oct 29, 2009 11:41 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
